  1. Train a linear regression model and evaluate the model 4.1 Train the model
set.seed(0)
training.samples <- df$Ozone.S %>%
  createDataPartition(p = 0.8, list = FALSE)
train.data  <- df[training.samples, ]
test.data <- df[-training.samples, ]

model <- lm(Ozone.S ~., data = train.data)
summary(model)

  1. Develop a Shiny application to predict the employment
library(shiny)
ui<- fluidPage(
titlePanel(title=" Air Quality Prediction "),
sidebarLayout(
sidebarPanel(
  sliderInput('solar', 'Solar Radiation', min=7, max=334, value=7, step=1, round=0),
  sliderInput('wind', 'Wind', min=2, max=21, value=2, step=1, round=0),
  sliderInput('temp', 'Temperature', min=55, max=100, value=1, step=0.1, round=0),
  selectInput('month', 'Month', c('May', 'Jun', 'Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep')),
  selectInput('day', 'Day', c(1:31)),
),
mainPanel(
  h3(textOutput('title')),
  verbatimTextOutput('result')
))
)
## Warning: In sliderInput(): `value` should be greater than or equal to `min`
## (value = 1, min = 55).
server<- function (input, output){
  data <- reactive({
    data.frame(Solar.R=input$solar,
               Wind=input$wind,
               Temp=input$temp,
               Month=input$month,
               Day=input$day,
               Ozone=0
               )
  })
  
  prediction <- reactive({
    predict(model, newdata = data())
  })
  
  t <- "Predicted Air Quality:"
  
  output$title <- renderText(t)

  output$result <- renderText(prediction())
}

shinyApp (ui = ui , server = server )
